How the pandemic will end.
The Atlantic’s Ed Yong offers up tough truths that preserve in amber the uncertainties and realities of this strange moment.
Though the onset of this crisis may have seemed fast, particularly in the US, pulling ourselves out of it will likely be anything but.
Americans are reminded of the sobering fact that our system has failed in most of the ways that count, shattering the illusion of our superiority.
—Alexandra Ossola, special projects editorRead more on The Atlantic